tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All measured parameters are within normal limits except for a slightly low HbA1c, which may suggest recent hypoglycemia or tight glycemic control. Glucose is at the lower end of normal. Renal function, electrolytes, and calcium are unremarkable. No acute laboratory abnormalities detected; clinical correlation recommended, especially regarding glycemic management.
